&lt;td&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Medrio Senior Site Reliability Engineer, you will be a part of the ITOps group responsible for maintaining all environments supporting the SDLC for Medrio’s platform.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Duties and Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build, maintain, and support all environments which host the Medrio Platform&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor environments for issues, configuring and building alerting/self-healing of issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Update and maintain documentation and architectural diagrams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with developers and testers to troubleshoot application/platform issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and implement architectural solutions to solve problems and support features&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentor junior level engineers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Competencies&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Kubernetes and Service mesh management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Windows and Linux administration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cloud service provider experience (GCP, Azure, AWS, Oracle Cloud)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic Oracle, SQL Server, or other relational database administration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Scripting (Powershell, Bash)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Configuration management (Jenkins, Helm, Ansible)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;.NET application management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to be creative as well as analytical, organized and detail oriented when problem-solving&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with AI/ML tools for automation, observability, predictive maintenance, and incident management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong verbal and written communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong leadership, project management and people skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Natural curiosity and self-motivation to learn and keep current on technical skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High energy level combined with good organization and multi-tasking skills necessary to achieve a changing mix of short, medium, and long-term objectives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Medrio:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Medrio, we look for smart, capable, and conscientious people to help us expand our product capabilities, grow our business, and better serve our customers. Our employees love working for us because they get to develop, market, and sell a product that advances human health, and they enjoy many perks, including&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Great benefits: We offer medical, dental, vision, and life/LTD insurance, and we cover 100% of our employees’ health insurance premiums and 50% of dependent premiums.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Wellness: Medrio values our staff’s well-being. To prove it, we promote an atmosphere of work/life balance, including flexible work schedules and locations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Weekly company-wide standup.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Medrio team is made up of individuals with a wide array of skills and interests, but all have a passion for providing the best possible user experience for our customers. We value collaboration, ingenuity and creating a culture of excellence!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary Range: $170,000 - 190,000 USD&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;To see detailed information on the data we collect during the application process, and how Medrio complies with data privacy laws, visit our&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://medrio.com/about/#careers&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Careers&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;page.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;table&gt;
&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reporting to the CEO and serving on the Executive Leadership Team (ELT), the Senior Vice President of Engineering leads Engineering, Test, IT Operations, and Deployment teams. Working closely with Product Management, this role is responsible for driving Medrio’s AI-first engineering strategy, delivering software that customers trust, and building the high-performance team and technical infrastructure needed. The VP of Engineering owns architecture, security posture, delivery standards, and the engineering organization’s culture, talent, and operational health.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Duties and Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AI &amp;amp; Architecture&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive adoption of AI-assisted development (AIAD) across the engineering org — from rapid prototyping to enterprise-grade production software&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own cloud-native architecture decisions across a multi-product SaaS platform; build modular, multi-tenant systems that maximize common platform reuse&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify where AI creates distinct, defensible advantages in the product and SDLC&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Delivery &amp;amp; Operations&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive consistent, methodology-agnostic delivery (Scrum, Kanban, Hybrid); own the Definition of Done&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead IT operations and deployment/release engineering — own system uptime, incident response, and release integrity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate raw delivery data and JIRA metrics into strategic insights for the ELT&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Optimize the development lifecycle by eliminating bottlenecks and automating repetitive workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Security &amp;amp; Regulatory Stewardship&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own Medrio’s security posture and ensure on-time renewal of ISO 27001/27701, SOC 2, HIPAA, and GDPR&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage regulatory compliance proactively — GxP, 21 CFR Part 11, and evolving requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Stakeholder &amp;amp; Influence&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with the VP of Product on roadmap tradeoffs and shared accountability for launch outcomes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interact with customers, strategic partners, and the Board to shape opportunities and roadmaps&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Negotiate vendor, cloud, offshore, and customer commercial contracts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support new investment in Medrio and company acquisition through technical due diligence&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;People Leadership&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead a mixed org of engineering directors, senior managers, and senior ICs (staff/principal engineers) simultaneously&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain an A-player engineering team through structured performance management, recruiting, and active talent development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the engineering opex budget and long-range resource planning&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SMB Market Focus&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Position Medrio as the fastest-to-deploy, easiest-to-use platform in the SMB clinical trial market&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Resist scope creep from large-customer requests that distract from the core SMB product strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Customers or Clients&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;CEO and Executive Leadership Team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Board of Directors (as needed)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;VP of Product and product leadership&lt;/li&gt;
